The latest data from NetMarketShare shows that Windows 7 remains comfortably ahead of Windows 10 on desktop PCs. Its March 2018 statistics also showed that iOS 11.2 and Android 7.0 are the most popular mobile operating systems, with 20.93% and 20.41% market share respectively. Android 8.0 has also gained market share since its launch in August 2017, but remains at below 5% of total operating system share on mobile. The most popular operating systems on desktop and mobile for March 2018 are detailed below.  